args: I remember the first time I saw her,\njust before the Dragon Choosing...
Why have you come here? If you knew\nthe powers you were trifling with...
I will stop you from forging this\ndragonpact, no matter the cost!
But that would not be the last time\nshe appeared before us...
Forgive me. My journey ends in failure;\nI was unable to avert a future of misery.
But next time... If I might be granted just\none more chance...
Etch these words into your heart, Brother,\nfor there will come a time when you\nmust decide.
Do not worry about my life.\nSeek the Dawnshard for your own.
I saw that second Zethia disappear\nbefore my eyes, and yet...
Stop! You musn't use that power further!
Since I am not of this world,\nit seems only right that I be\nthe one to change my name.
Now she's appeared before us again,\nand has a new name—Zena.
Zena is Zethia from another world.\nBut what possible business could\nshe have HERE? On OUR world?
You're a Zethia from another world.\nThat much I understand.
But why are you here?\nWhat do you want?
And how did you even get here in the\nfirst place? Repeatedly visiting one\nspecific world is no easy matter.
And then there is the issue of your mana.
She is... Well, I was going to say\n＂enveloped in mana,＂ but that is\nnot quite accurate.
Better to say that she IS mana.
She's comprised of mana?\nIt's as if she's a ghost...
I have come here from another world;\none that has proceeded on a different\npath than your own.
On that world, I used the Dawnshard—
Do not worry about my life.\nSeek the Dawnshard for your own.
You told us to go after the Dawnshard.
I know little of the Dawnshard, but I do\nknow that the space between worlds\nconnects to a vast multitude of worlds.
To locate and reach a specific world\nfrom among that number would be\na monumental task.
Does this Dawnshard truly\npossess this level of power?
Yeah, yeah, we all wanna hear about the\nmagical widget, but first, I wanna know\nwhere the heck you've BEEN!
I mean, you just sorta vanished from the\nBinding Ruins, and now you're here?
Seems like a long trip to just\ncome visit us, ya know?
Gimme all ya got, is what we're sayin'.

And yeah, I get that some'a this stuff
might be uncomfortable, but we gotta
know what we're puttin' our butts on
the line for here.
I understand. If we are to fight together,\nit is only fair I tell you everything.
So I will share my story now,\nbut would ask you to steel yourselves.
Because there are parts you may wish\nyou had never heard.
Nevertheless, I swear that all I am\nabout to say is the truth.
It is an unvarnished account of events\nthat have transpired in worlds apart\nfrom your own.
Pray bear that in mind as you listen.
Then I shall begin my\nlong and lonely tale.
And tell you of the many worlds\nI visited on my way here...
